All Classes

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    App
    App is the base class where the application starts.
    Category
    Model class of the categories of tasks.
    Client
    Model class of the clients.
    ControllerAddingEditingSuper
    This is the super class of ControllerTaskEditing and ControllerTaskAdding.
    ControllerAdjustments
    This class controls the user adjustments like account, password and user image changes.
    ControllerEvaluation
    Controls a handful of visual task evaluation diagrams that should help the user with keeping overview.
    ControllerLogin
    This class controls the login view and is the interface to the main view.
    ControllerMain
    This class controls the main view.
    ControllerOfTasks
    This class contains all parent components and operations of the tasks.
    ControllerSignUp
    This class controls the sign up view and is the interface to the main view.
    ControllerStart
    This class controls the start view and contains functionality to get to login and sign up area.
    ControllerSuperTasks
    This class is the abstrace base class of all tasks.
    ControllerTaskAdding
    Controls the window you can add task information.
    ControllerTaskEditing
    Controls the the window you can edit task information.
    ControllerTaskManipulation
    This class contains functionality for filtering, sorting and adding tasks.
    ControllerTasksDone
    Controls the actions for done tasks that means deleting or rebuilding.
    ControllerTasksUndone
    Controls the actions for open tasks that means checking, deleting or editing.
    ControllerWelcome
    This class controls the welcome view.
    DBConnection
    This class contains all of the database operations.
    FieldValidation
    Contains all of the information needed for validation, no matter what pattern it should be.
    Priority
    Model class of the task priorities.
    Session
    Loads and contains all the database content which corresponds to the client.
    SubCategory
    Model class of the task subcategories.
    Task
    Model class of the tasks.
